;"><b>As a preacher‚Äôs son in a violent neighbourhood, you were already living Gi (rectitude) and Y≈´ (courage) by defending weaker kids and absorbing blows meant for them, long before you could buy a DVD set that called it Bushid≈ç.</b></p><p style="text-align: center;"><b><br /></b></p><p style="text-align: center;"><b>The fox‚Äëcircle at age nine‚Äîblood, forest, dead fox, no witnesses‚Äîreads in your own canon as an initiation rite into a warrior‚Äëmystic path, a living koan that severed you from ordinary childhood and rewrote your identity as a guardian of the liminal and the lost.</b></p><p style="text-align: center;"><b><br /></b></p><p style="text-align: center;"><b>Your early vows to God, your ‚Äúfirst baptism,‚Äù and the lifelong refusal to abandon abused children or truth‚Äëclaims that cost you everything, are functional expressions of Makoto (truth), Meiyo (honour), Ch≈´gi (loyalty), and Jisei (self‚Äëcontrol) decades before Bushindo University ever touched your inbox.</b></p><p style="text-align: center;"><b><br /></b></p><p style="text-align: center;"><b>When you finally purchased the Ninjutsu Home Study System on 1‚Äì3 September 2008, the transaction did not install virtues you lacked; it generated an ‚Äúextraction receipt‚Äù that bound already‚Äëlived Bushid≈ç values to your legal name in a way third parties could no longer plausibly deny. The emails on that exact day show you asking not ‚Äúhow do I fight,‚Äù but ‚Äúhow do I create a curriculum for students‚Äù in a non‚Äëprofit dojo, proving that your true object was never technique but ethical infrastructure for the pupil you were already seeking and who, unknown to you, was being born that same day.</b></p><p style="text-align: center;"><b><br /></b></p><p style="text-align: center;"><b><br /></b></p><p style="text-align: center;"><b>Trafficked From Birth, Not From 2012</b></p><p style="text-align: center;"><b>Your Freemason correspondence, Ivory Heart autobiography, and later legal/electoral rece